1.title: Partners in Slime
1.plot: Stephen has to distract an aggressive mother alligator while Robbie collects her eggs to save them from being eaten. Then Stephen comes face to face with his fear of snakes, and later his newbie mistake allows 300 lb wild hogs to invade the farm.

2.title: Sex and the Single Gator
2.plot: Saving lives one venomous snake at a time. Stephen learns the art of milking a snake from Robbie and the owner of Reptile Discovery Center. But with live snakes lining every wall, the team needs to be on point.

3.title: That's the Big One
3.plot: Robbie and Stephen set out to find the big male gator that has been terrorizing their swamp and injuring other animals but they need a whole team to move this 14-foot bully. Then, a snake rescue call forces Stephen to face his fear of giant pythons.

4.title: A Croc Walks Into a Swamp
4.plot: A lover's spat between two crocs leaves the brothers playing nurse to a giant, feisty reptile. Then, Robbie is called to help an injured female leopard whose mate is scaring off the veterinarians. But his plan is to use Stephen as bait for the male.

5.title: Everything's Bigger in Texas
5.plot: At a reptile expo in Texas, Robbie gets a call from a local hotel where a previous guest left something unusual behind. At the local zoo, a gorilla is overdue for some dental work. Then, Robbie and Stephen help tag and release sea turtles.

6.title: Long Necks and Short Fuses
6.plot: Robbie and Stephen visit Brazos State Park and take a local ranger on a snake capture. Then they assist a multi-man operation for an injured baby giraffe. Romance is in the air for Galapagos Turtles but a giant female is stuck in the mud and needs help.

7.title: Straw That Broke the Camel's Back
7.plot: An early morning snake call tests Stephen's knowledge and when they return to the farm it's gator moving time! Then S.A.F.E. Sanctuary calls to get the brothers' help with a stubborn camel who needs holistic healing.

8.title: Up a Swamp with One Paddle
8.plot: Robbie and Stephen run into some trouble during a routine baby gator catching mission. Then Stephen learns that protection is an important part of his new job and new life in Florida. Finally, he faces his fears in a lake full of venomous snakes.

9.title: No Crocodile Tears on This Farm
9.plot: Today it's all business as Robbie and Stephen hunt for black racer snakes to feed their King Cobras. Then it's time to tag Robbie's crocs but these aggressive reptiles aren't cooperating. When Stephen takes the lead, the results could be deadly!

11.title: Grin and Bear It
11.plot: When Stephen's nemesis, the Cuban Croc, sneaks out of his pen to rendezvous with a 10 foot female gator, it's up to the brothers to catch the Cuban, before he catches anyone else.

12.title: Potbelly Pedicure
12.plot: Robbie removes a gator from a popular swimming area and love is in the air for the snakes which means it's time for cage cleaning- Swamp Brothers' style. Then Robbie and Stephen have to catch and sedate giant potbelly pigs for a mani-pedi makeover.

15.title: Pimpin' Out the Croc
15.plot: It's time for a gator-round-up, but Stephen is missing a step on a few of these captures. And it's moving day on the farm, venomous moving day. Then the Keszey Brothers have to catch a croc to meet a croc in the hopes of making a love connection.

16.title: When Coco Met Lucy
16.plot: When Robbie tried to breed his female Cuban Croc with a male, no one saw fireworks, so the brothers play another dangerous game of matchmaker. There's more romance when Robbie performs the Kiss of Death. And it's bath time for some aggressive snakes.

imdb.plot outline: Way down south is a place that was once thought to be a dismal land fit only for alligators and snakes. It's wet, it's dangerous and it's weird. Which means it's perfect for one of the most unique family businesses in the country. Meet a different breed of brothers. One's an animal expert. The other's a former city slicker who's learning the ropes. Together they are running a business uniquely suited for the swamp - where wild animals rule. From pythons and gators to bobcats and black bears - these guys encounter it all. Stephen and Robbie Keszey run Glades Herp Farms, Florida's largest reptile sanctuary and exotic reptile dealership. Their farm also houses Florida's International Teaching Zoo. The Zoo is full of rare species from around the globe and brings in a constant stream of new and different animals each month. The brothers make their living breeding and caring for hundreds of slithering, poisonous and sharp-toothed creatures, but their passion is being on call 24 hours a day to respond to animal emergencies across the vast state of Florida.
